Name: OffsetMany
Description: Create one or more curves by offsetting a planar curve by the given distance in a plane defined by the plane normal. If there are gaps between the offset component curves then, they are filled by extending the offset curves. The "planeNormal" input argument defaults to the normal of the plane containing the curve but an explicit normal parallel to the original curve normal can be provided to better control the direction of the offset. For example, if a consistent offset direction is required for multiple curves sharing the same plane, the "planeNormal" can be used to override individual curve normals and force all curves to be offset in the same direction. Reversing the normal reverses the direction of the offset.

Description: Transform a slab shape based on a list of Points

Name: FootingType.BreaksAtInserts

Description: Finds the furthest entity in a list of geometric entities from another given entity

Description: Returns UV coordinates, XYZ coordinates and normals for a face with UV subdivision

Name: Grid.InvertAndMirrorNormalizedValues
Description: Inverts and mirrors (horizontally & vertically) a nested list of normalized values.

Name: Grid.Plane
Description: Retrieves the plane of a grid. Returns null for curved grid lines.

Name: Group.FromElements
Description: Creates a group from a list of Revit elements. Unlike the OOTB node, it supports naming the created group directly and also indicates which of the input elements (if any) could not be grouped.

The node will likely report null for group instances where members have been excluded but subsequently been restored.

Name: Group.Members
Description: Retrieves the members of a group. ATTENTION: This node will be deprecated in 2023. Please switch to the OOTB node Group.GetMembers.

Name: Group.Ungroup
Description: Ungroups a group and returns a boolean and the ungrouped elements. Unlike with the OOTB node, returning the ungrouped elements can be turned off for better performance when dealing with large numbers of groups.

Name: GroupType.Groups
Description: Returns all group instances of a given group type

Name: Hex.FromDecimal

Name: Hex.ToDecimal
Description: Converts a string of a hexadecimal value to a number

Name: ImportInstance.IsLinked

Name: InternalUnit.ToDisplayUnit
Description: Converts a value from Revit's internal unit to a given display unit

Name: IsEvenNumber
Description: Checks if a number is even.

Name: IsMultipleOf
Description: Checks if A is a multiple of B.

Name: IsOddNumber
Description: Checks if a number is odd.

Name: IsSimilar

Name: Level.Plane

Name: Level.Views
Description: Returns all views associated with a given level

Name: List.CountOccurences
Description: Counts the number of occurences of each unique element in a given list

Name: List.DropLastItem
Description: Drops the last item from a given list.

Name: List.EqualSublistLengths
Description: Trims all given lists to the length of the shortest list

Name: List.FilterBySublistLength
Description: Filters out all sublists that do not have the specified length

Name: List.GroupListOfListsByKey
Description: Groups a list of lists by one of its keys

Name: List.IsNotEmpty
Description: Just the inversion of the built-in Is Empty List node.

Name: List.JoinByKey
Description: Joins two lists by common keys.

Name: List.MatchWithKeyValues
Description: Matches a list with a given set of keys and returns the values corresponding to the keys

Name: List.ReplaceEmptyLists
Description: Replaces all empty lists within a given list with a substitute

Name: List.ReplaceItemAtIndex+
Description: Replaces the item at a given index of a list by another item. Unlike the OOTB node, it can replace items at multiple indeces.

Name: List.ReplaceNull
Description: Replaces all null values within a given list with a substitute

Name: List.SortListOfLists
Description: Sorts a list of lists by one of its sublists

Name: List.WithLeadingZeroes
Description: Adds leading zeros to a sequence of numbers

Name: MassFloor.Mass

Name: Morse.FromAlphanumeric

Name: Morse.ToAlphanumeric
Description: Converts a string in Morse code to alphanumeric

Name: Normalization.InvertNormalized
Description: Inverts a value between 0 and 1 to its opposite (1-x)

Name: Normalization.Normalize
Description: Converts a value into a normalized value according to a value range

Name: Normalization.NormalizeRange
Description: Normalizes a range of numbers

Name: Normalization.ScaleNormalized
Description: Scales a normalized value according to a given minimum and maximum

Name: NormalizedSequence.ByFunction

Name: NormalizedSequence.ByNumber
Description: Creates a sequence of N values between 0 and 1

Name: Object.Members
Description: Gets a list of all members (properties and methods) of a selected element

Name: Object.MembersByName
Description: Looks up all the members of a given element based on a given name (or part of a name) of the property or method. Search is case-insensitive.

Name: ParameterElement.SetAllowVaryBetweenGroups
Description: Lets you define whether or not the values of a given project parameter can vary across group members.

Name: ParameterFilterElement.FilterRuleString
Description: Aggregates the filter rules of a given ParameterFilterElement into a human-readable string

Name: ParameterFilterElement.Parameters
Description: Retrieves the names of all parameters used in a given ParameterFilterElement (aka view filters)

Name: Part.SourceElement
Description: Retrieves the element a given part was made from

Name: Passthrough
Description: Forces a sequential order of execution. The node wired into the output of the Passthrough node will be executed *after* the node wired into the waitFor input (e.g. important for some Revit operations). The value of the passThrough input will be passed on to the node wired into the output port of the Passthrough node.

Name: PathGraph.AllPaths
Description: Finds all possible paths between two nodes.  The connections input expects a list of value pairs.

Name: PathGraph.ByPairs
Description: Builds a path graph (Python dictionary) from a list of value pairs.

Name: PathGraph.ShortestPath
Description: Finds the shortest path (fewest steps) between two nodes. The connections input expects a list of value pairs.

Name: Pattern.TriangularFlatDiagonal
Description: Creates groups of points from a list of UVs or XYZs for the placement of triangular panels. The placement pattern can be reversed (boolean) and shifted (integer).

Name: Pattern.TriangularFlatMirrored
Description: Creates groups of points from a list of UVs or XYZs for the placement of triangular (diagrid) panels. The placement pattern can be reversed (boolean) and shifted (integer).

Name: PerspectiveView.OrientToEyeAndTargetPosition
Description: Sets the orientation of a given perspective view based on a given eye and target position. View needs to be in an unlocked state.

Name: Plane.ByBestFitFromFace
Description: Creates a plane from face

Name: Plane.ByFirst3Points
Description: Returns a plane, its origin and its normal based on the first three XYZs in a given list

Name: Plane.IsCoplanarWithPlane
Description: Checks if a given plane is coplanar with another plane

Name: PlanView.Underlay
Description: Returns the underlay(s) of a given plan view

Name: Point.Average

Description: Projects a list of points onto a given plane

Description: Rounds a point coordinate to a specified precision

Description: Rounds a point coordinate *up* to a specified precision

Description: Retrieves the furthest point in a sequence of points

Name: PointSequences.ShortestPath
Description: Retrieves the shortest path from a number of point sequences

Description: Creates a railing based on a given path, railing type and level.

Description: Creates a list of random integers between 0 and a given maximum value

Name: Regex.ContainsRegularExpression

Determines if a regular expression matches a string (or a list of strings), i.e. occurs anywhere in the string, and returns a boolean value (or a list, depending on the input). The syntax for regular expressions is explained at

Name: Regex.FindRegularExpression
Description:

http://ironpython-test.readthedocs.org/en/latest/howto/regex.html

Name: Regex.ReplaceRegularExpression

http://ironpython-test.readthedocs.org/en/latest/howto/regex.html

Name: Regex.SplitByRegularExpression
Description:
Splits a given string by a regular expression. The syntax for regular expressions is explained at
http://ironpython-test.readthedocs.org/en/latest/howto/regex.html

Name: Regex.StartsWithRegularExpression
Description:
Determines if a string starts with the regular expression and returns a boolean value (or a list, depending on the input). The syntax for regular expressions is explained at
http://ironpython-test.readthedocs.org/en/latest/howto/regex.html

Name: ReturnListOrSingleValue

Description: Returns the underlying Revit face reference of a given surface

Description: Returns the path type of a RevitLInkType

Description: Creates an unplaced room

Description: Retrieves all windows that are associated with a room (hosted in walls and roofs).

Description: Creates room separation lines from geometry curves.

Name: RoomSequence.ToDoorSequence
Description: Retrieves a sequence of doors connecting a given sequence of rooms (if possible)

Description: Changes the family type of a given room tag to the specified type

Description: Rounds a number to a specified precision

Name: SelectionSet.Elements

Description: Returns all parameters from a shared parameter file.

Description: Creates placeholder sheets

Description: Returns the scale of a given sheet

Description: Returns all schedules placed on a specified sheet ATTENTION: This node will be deprecated in 2024. As of Revit 2022, please switch to the OOTB node of the same name.

Name: SpaceSeparator.FromCurve
Description: Creates space separation lines from geometry curves.

Description: Places a spot coordinate at a given point in a given view. May not work in all view types.

Name: SpotElevation.ByPoint
Description: Places a spot elevation at a given point in a given view. May not work in all view types.

Name: String.Explode

Description: Replaces all characters in a string that are illegal characters for Revit view names etc.

Description: Replaces multiple search terms in a given string with multiple replacements

Description: Retrieves the kind of a given structural foundation (isolated, wall, slab).

Description: Creates a new subcategory for a given element category (unless a subcategory of that name already exists - in that case it returns the existing subcategory).

Description: Sorts surfaces in three lists based on their orientation (vertical, horizontal up & horizontal down) and also returns three corresponding lists of booleans.

Name: Surface.IsPlanar
Description: Checks whether a face is planar

Name: Switch
Description: Emulates the Switch/Case statement that is  available in multiple programming languages.

Name: System.CPUs
Description: Returns information on number of processors and CPU speed (GHz).

Name: System.MachineName
Description: Returns the NetBIOS name of the computer the script is executed on.

Description: Returns information on total system memory, free memory and amount of memory used by the application.

Description: Returns the user name of the person who is currently logged on to Windows on the machine the script is executed on.

Name: System.Version

Description: Rounds a UV coordinate to a specified precision

Name: Vector.CorrectOrientation
Description: Inverts vector A if its inversion is closer to vector B

Name: Vector.IntersectWithPlane
Description: Finds the intersection point between a plane and a vector

Name: Vector.IntersectWithVector
Description: Determines if two vectors intersect and returns the closest points of intersection on both vectors.

Name: Vector.IsInPlane

Name: Vector.IsOrthogonalToVector
Description: Checks if two vectors are orthogonal to each other

Name: Vector.IsParallelToPlane
Description: Checks if a given vector is parallel to a given plane

Name: Vector.PruneDuplicates
Description: Prune vectors to exclude duplicates within a given tolerance

Description: Returns an XYZ of 0,0,-1
